<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-21T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/608a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in Certain
                                        Countries</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d119fn1">Those in Central and South America
                                    and in Norway, Sweden, Denmar the Netherlands, Spain, and
                                    Switzerland.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-21T20:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Before sending recommendations for the addition of names to the enemy
                                trading list or for removals therefrom, confer with the British and
                                French diplomatic representatives in the country to which you are
                                accredited. Such action will further our purposes of common counsel
                                and cooperation.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>